262
00:20:17,738 --> 00:20:21,033
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

263
00:20:21,116 --> 00:20:23,076
Please try again later.

264
00:20:29,958 --> 00:20:31,251
HA-JOON

265
00:20:33,795 --> 00:20:34,629
No!

266
00:20:35,130 --> 00:20:36,006
No, Haetsal!

267
00:20:37,674 --> 00:20:39,384
When the door closes, you're done.

268
00:20:39,468 --> 00:20:42,846
At least you should get out
so we can find a way, right?

269
00:20:43,347 --> 00:20:46,558
The person you are trying to reach
is unavailable.

270
00:20:46,641 --> 00:20:48,560
Please try again later.

271
00:20:49,853 --> 00:20:52,272
SE-AH, I FOUND A WAY
THERE'S A WAY TO STOP THE TIMER

272
00:20:53,815 --> 00:20:57,069
AND I HAVE SOMETHING TO CONFESS TO YOU

273
00:20:57,152 --> 00:21:00,822
HYEONG-WOOK ACTUALLY…

274
00:21:11,166 --> 00:21:12,459
YOO SE-AH

275
00:21:13,668 --> 00:21:16,421
GEON-WOO, I FOUND A WAY TO STOP THE TIMER!

276
00:21:18,757 --> 00:21:20,300
BUT KEEP THIS A SECRET FROM NA-RI

277
00:21:20,384 --> 00:21:22,260
NOT ALL THREE OF US CAN MAKE IT OUT ALIVE

278
00:21:27,474 --> 00:21:30,769
HOW DO YOU STOP IT?

279
00:21:32,771 --> 00:21:35,023
I'LL TELL YOU IN PERSON, WAIT

280
00:21:45,283 --> 00:21:47,244
What the hell could it be?

281
00:21:50,914 --> 00:21:52,290
YOO SE-AH

282
00:22:00,215 --> 00:22:01,049
Damn it!

283
00:22:17,774 --> 00:22:20,485
Should I dig into Ha-joon
instead of Se-ah?

284
00:22:22,028 --> 00:22:25,490
They're both ignoring me,
so they've gotta be together.

285
00:23:40,065 --> 00:23:42,943
Hey, what are you doing here?

286
00:23:43,443 --> 00:23:45,737
Se-ah's aunt asked me to run an errand.

287
00:23:45,820 --> 00:23:47,405
What about you?

288
00:23:47,489 --> 00:23:48,907
Let's talk inside.

289
00:23:55,830 --> 00:23:58,542
If you're gonna do that all day,
I'm going home.

290
00:23:58,625 --> 00:23:59,501
Give me my phone.

291
00:24:05,257 --> 00:24:07,717
I remembered something
while watching your video.

292
00:24:07,801 --> 00:24:09,553
I saw someone that day.

293
00:24:16,810 --> 00:24:17,936
Up there.

294
00:24:19,437 --> 00:24:20,897
There was someone else there.

295
00:24:27,279 --> 00:24:28,863
What are you doing? It's scary.

296
00:24:29,864 --> 00:24:31,950
She had a huge wound on her face,

297
00:24:32,534 --> 00:24:36,746
and the same uniform and name tag as us,
but she didn't seem familiar.

298
00:24:37,455 --> 00:24:40,083
A huge wound on her face?

299
00:24:40,834 --> 00:24:41,668
Yeah.

300
00:24:42,794 --> 00:24:44,004
Strange.

301
00:24:44,087 --> 00:24:46,881
If she were in our grade,
we would've at least heard about it.

302
00:24:47,382 --> 00:24:49,217
Wanna go to the school with me tonight?

303
00:24:51,511 --> 00:24:52,345
Tonight?

304
00:24:52,429 --> 00:24:55,056
I need to check something
without the teachers finding out,

305
00:24:55,140 --> 00:24:58,226
but I'm a little uncomfortable
going by myself.

306
00:24:58,727 --> 00:25:00,520
Could you help me?

307
00:25:04,065 --> 00:25:05,066
Sure.

308
00:25:06,109 --> 00:25:07,485
But I can't go like this.

309
00:25:07,569 --> 00:25:08,820
Pick a time and place.

310
00:25:08,903 --> 00:25:10,071
I'll change and meet you.

311
00:25:10,155 --> 00:25:12,365
Okay. Thanks, Na-ri.

312
00:25:17,329 --> 00:25:19,539
The signal was last detected

313
00:25:20,415 --> 00:25:23,043
at Gwangdong Apartments, Building 323.

314
00:25:23,126 --> 00:25:25,170
But I can't confirm the floor number.

315
00:25:25,253 --> 00:25:26,963
So is the phone off right now?

316
00:25:27,047 --> 00:25:28,256
That would be my guess.

317
00:25:28,340 --> 00:25:32,344
Nowadays, as long as the phone's on,
it'll pick up either Wi-Fi or GPS.

318
00:25:36,931 --> 00:25:38,850
WHERE ARE YOU?

319
00:25:38,933 --> 00:25:42,646
WHEN ARE WE MEETING UP?

320
00:25:47,192 --> 00:25:48,777
YOU'LL FIND OUT SOON, NO RUSH

321
00:25:48,860 --> 00:25:51,112
GEON-WOO
I'M THE ONE WHO STOPPED YOUR TIMER :)

322
00:26:00,038 --> 00:26:05,669
ARE WE STILL KEEPING IT A SECRET
FROM NA-RI?

323
00:26:09,547 --> 00:26:12,258
YEAH, NOT ALL THREE OF US
CAN MAKE IT OUT ALIVE

324
00:26:33,738 --> 00:26:35,782
Geon-woo, wait for me.

325
00:26:36,366 --> 00:26:38,451
How did you know
about the hole in the fence?

326
00:26:38,535 --> 00:26:39,619
I made it.

327
00:26:39,703 --> 00:26:41,037
Huh? Why would you do that?

328
00:26:41,705 --> 00:26:43,415
To get Se-ah on the national team.

329
00:26:44,082 --> 00:26:44,916
Come on. Let's go.

330
00:26:50,422 --> 00:26:53,758
Hey, why are we going this way?
The path's right there.

331
00:26:55,343 --> 00:26:56,386
Be careful coming down.

332
00:26:56,469 --> 00:26:57,470
Okay.

333
00:27:03,101 --> 00:27:04,644
-What's that?
-This?

334
00:27:05,729 --> 00:27:06,771
Just a decoration.

335
00:27:12,527 --> 00:27:13,820
Hey, what are you doing?

336
00:27:20,410 --> 00:27:22,454
Getting a kid on the national team
isn't easy.

337
00:27:25,790 --> 00:27:26,791
Let's go in.

338
00:27:40,597 --> 00:27:42,056
Man, you scared me.

339
00:28:02,452 --> 00:28:04,287
When did you and Se-ah start going out?

340
00:28:08,208 --> 00:28:09,417
We're not.

341
00:28:09,501 --> 00:28:10,335
Yeah, right.

342
00:28:10,418 --> 00:28:13,505
Earlier, you punched in Se-ah's passcode
and walked right in.

343
00:28:13,588 --> 00:28:16,424
You're close enough
to know each other's passcodes.

344
00:28:17,008 --> 00:28:18,176
That was only because--

345
00:28:18,259 --> 00:28:20,637
That wish video you made
while eating chicken

346
00:28:21,137 --> 00:28:23,056
was at Se-ah's place.

347
00:28:24,098 --> 00:28:26,434
It looked like Ha-joon caught on too.

348
00:28:28,561 --> 00:28:33,775
I'm just curious if that's what happens
when you sneak around every night.

349
00:28:34,359 --> 00:28:35,819
That's all.

350
00:28:38,613 --> 00:28:40,532
It's not like that. Well…

351
00:28:41,991 --> 00:28:45,119
It hasn't been that long.
I wasn't trying to hide it or anything.

352
00:28:45,203 --> 00:28:46,037
Sorry.

353
00:28:49,415 --> 00:28:52,544
You like each other, so you're dating.
Why apologize?

354
00:28:53,044 --> 00:28:54,629
I wasn't apologizing for us dating.

355
00:28:55,129 --> 00:28:58,383
I was apologizing
for lying to you just now.

356
00:29:00,343 --> 00:29:01,344
Unbelievable.

357
00:29:01,427 --> 00:29:03,471
Hey, I lie to you all the time.

358
00:29:03,555 --> 00:29:05,348
Why apologize for something like that?

359
00:29:05,932 --> 00:29:07,308
Like what, for example?

360
00:29:08,393 --> 00:29:09,227
Huh?

361
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:12,146
Name one lie you told me.

362
00:29:13,273 --> 00:29:14,774
Then what will you do for me?

363
00:29:16,609 --> 00:29:17,861
Whatever it is,

364
00:29:18,361 --> 00:29:19,988
I'll tell you it's okay.

365
00:29:28,204 --> 00:29:30,623
I lied about lying to you all the time.

366
00:29:31,291 --> 00:29:33,835
And the lie about that being a lie?
Also a lie.

367
00:29:37,380 --> 00:29:38,548
NURSE'S OFFICE

368
00:29:44,012 --> 00:29:45,763
We made it this far,

369
00:29:46,598 --> 00:29:47,932
but how do we get in?

370
00:29:53,897 --> 00:29:55,607
The nurse's office door is busted.

371
00:30:06,326 --> 00:30:08,745
So they really do keep these.

372
00:30:08,828 --> 00:30:13,291
So even years from now, they'd know
I was bumming around here twice a week?

373
00:30:13,374 --> 00:30:14,250
That's creepy.

374
00:30:14,334 --> 00:30:15,960
I hope there weren't kids like you.

375
00:30:21,507 --> 00:30:24,135
"Scraped knee, Choi Ju-a."

376
00:30:25,803 --> 00:30:28,181
"Suspected wrist sprain, Ju Da-hae."

377
00:30:33,811 --> 00:30:35,355
"Laceration with bleeding."

378
00:30:39,317 --> 00:30:40,360
"Kwon Si-won."

379
00:30:44,614 --> 00:30:45,448
Did you find it?

380
00:30:49,911 --> 00:30:51,037
Na-ri.

381
00:30:52,205 --> 00:30:54,248
She had a wound on her right cheek, right?

382
00:30:57,460 --> 00:30:58,753
You saw it too.

383
00:31:00,546 --> 00:31:01,756
That female student.

384
00:31:07,553 --> 00:31:10,139
I didn't notice it
the first time I watched your video.

385
00:31:10,640 --> 00:31:12,266
I realized it the second time.

386
00:31:13,893 --> 00:31:16,562
Why you kept moving the camera
while filming empty space.

387
00:31:17,188 --> 00:31:19,148
It seemed like
you saw the same thing I did.

388
00:31:21,943 --> 00:31:23,903
Something the others couldn't see.

389
00:31:34,914 --> 00:31:37,417
You said you were checking the video
to find your phone.

390
00:31:38,334 --> 00:31:41,004
So you were just pretending
you couldn't lie earlier?

391
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:44,757
Wow, Kim Geon-woo. This is new.

392
00:31:44,841 --> 00:31:46,801
Do you have my phone too?

393
00:31:46,884 --> 00:31:49,637
What if I told you I don't?
Would you believe me?

394
00:31:54,434 --> 00:31:55,268
Na-ri.

395
00:31:57,145 --> 00:32:01,399
I'm sure you had a valid reason
for the lies you told me.

396
00:32:02,608 --> 00:32:04,193
But from now on, let's be honest.

397
00:32:04,861 --> 00:32:05,778
Don't come closer!

398
00:32:06,779 --> 00:32:09,532
You brought me to an empty school
to scare me, didn't you?

399
00:32:09,615 --> 00:32:12,869
No, I just wanted to check
if you'd actually seen that girl.

400
00:32:13,453 --> 00:32:15,079
In case I was mistaken.

401
00:32:18,708 --> 00:32:20,668
Take one more step closer. I dare you.

402
00:32:27,633 --> 00:32:28,718
Brother-in-law.

403
00:32:39,270 --> 00:32:42,440
We're the only ones
who saw the girl in your video, Na-ri.

404
00:32:43,024 --> 00:32:44,484
That puts us in the most danger.

405
00:32:44,984 --> 00:32:49,030
You don't know what it's like
when she takes hold of you, do you?

406
00:32:49,697 --> 00:32:51,449
We need to help each other. Okay?

407
00:32:51,532 --> 00:32:53,576
I bet Se-ah can see her too now.

408
00:32:54,452 --> 00:32:55,495
What?

409
00:32:55,578 --> 00:32:58,414
A lot happened while you were out cold.

410
00:32:58,998 --> 00:33:01,125
You want to know
what kind of bitch Se-ah is?

411
00:33:05,129 --> 00:33:06,297
Do you see that?

412
00:33:06,380 --> 00:33:08,091
Some fucking friend she is.

413
00:33:08,883 --> 00:33:09,801
Na-ri.

414
00:33:10,468 --> 00:33:13,721
I went to the carrier this afternoon
and suspended my service.

415
00:33:14,222 --> 00:33:16,682
I reported it stolen,
signed out of all my accounts,

416
00:33:17,183 --> 00:33:18,559
and wiped my number clean.

417
00:33:18,643 --> 00:33:19,769
You get what I'm saying?

418
00:33:20,603 --> 00:33:22,647
No one can reach me
on that phone right now.

419
00:33:23,314 --> 00:33:25,358
That phone's bricked, Na-ri. Okay?

420
00:33:33,032 --> 00:33:34,534
You really did your homework.

421
00:33:35,243 --> 00:33:39,372
Hyeong-wook and I went through
the same thing, the calls and texts.

422
00:33:39,455 --> 00:33:41,124
Don't come any closer. Just listen!

423
00:33:41,833 --> 00:33:43,584
You know everything, huh?

424
00:33:45,336 --> 00:33:47,130
Then you must know what my wish was.

425
00:33:49,715 --> 00:33:51,634
"I wish for Choi Hyeong-wook to die."

426
00:33:51,717 --> 00:33:52,718
Hey.

427
00:33:53,636 --> 00:33:54,971
Don't lie to me.

428
00:33:55,054 --> 00:33:56,055
You're right.

429
00:33:57,098 --> 00:33:59,392
That's what I call a good lie.

430
00:34:00,768 --> 00:34:02,103
But guess what?

431
00:34:02,645 --> 00:34:04,397
I even have the wish video here.

432
00:34:08,526 --> 00:34:09,902
Hey, are you okay?

433
00:34:09,986 --> 00:34:11,445
Don't come closer!

434
00:34:27,211 --> 00:34:28,754
I told you not to come any closer.

435
00:34:32,300 --> 00:34:33,134
Na-ri!

436
00:34:34,552 --> 00:34:35,595
Lim Na-ri!

437
00:34:57,909 --> 00:34:58,910
Why won't the door…

438
00:35:08,753 --> 00:35:09,712
Hey.

439
00:35:16,928 --> 00:35:17,762
Na-ri!

440
00:35:17,845 --> 00:35:19,972
Hey, Lim Na-ri!

441
00:35:33,486 --> 00:35:34,362
GIRIGO
DOWNLOAD

442
00:35:38,366 --> 00:35:40,826
BEGIN DOWNLOAD

443
00:36:19,657 --> 00:36:20,992
Hey!

444
00:36:54,358 --> 00:36:55,401
Don't do that.

445
00:38:27,034 --> 00:38:28,327
-Are you okay?
-Huh?

446
00:38:29,203 --> 00:38:30,621
Where's the girl you were with?

447
00:38:32,039 --> 00:38:33,666
The one you were yelling for!

448
00:38:33,749 --> 00:38:34,834
Who are you?

449
00:38:42,174 --> 00:38:43,092
Stay still.

450
00:38:47,221 --> 00:38:48,848
Huh? Are you okay?

451
00:39:10,494 --> 00:39:11,871
Done.

452
00:39:13,456 --> 00:39:14,290
Huh?

453
00:39:14,373 --> 00:39:15,541
What's going on?

454
00:39:30,431 --> 00:39:31,348
Have you ever heard

455
00:39:31,432 --> 00:39:33,642
that if you write down your saju
and make a wish…

456
00:39:36,479 --> 00:39:37,813
it'll come true?

457
00:43:21,704 --> 00:43:24,456
Subtitle translation by: Sung In Jang
